  <span id="freeText3443414121203459657" style="display:none">For de Sade, this is pretty good. There's a long discussion of the role of morals in the republic that is interesting, if debatable. As erotica, it is strictly chinese menu stuff. Bob'll have erotic act number one, Sally number two, and the Chevalier two orders of number seven, and then we'll all trade cartons. The interesting bit (to me) is that, even after copious pronouncements about how libertines transgress all boundaries, there's still a scene where Dolmance and Augustin go off in the corner to do something "so sinful" neither the women in the room nor the reader is allowed to know of it. Makes me wonder if de Sade ran out of ideas...</span>
